<head>PCT 34 - The Pock-Mark Cure</head>
<docauthor>Mrs. Maggie Achenam</docauthor>

<p n="1">

<seg n="1.1">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="kotak" class="pr" gcat="0sPR" sgloss="other" stem="kotak">kotak</w>
.
<gloss>Now another story.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="2">

<seg n="2.1">
<w canon="êsa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="reportedly" stem="êsa">êsa</w>
<w canon="mîna" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="also" stem="mîna">mînah</w>
<w canon="sipwêhtêpayiw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="go_off" stem="sipwêhtêpayi" suffix="-w">sipwêhtêpayiw</w>
<w canon="ê-pêyakot" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="be_alone" stem="pêyako" suffix="-t">êh-pâyakot</w>
,
<w canon="ê-nêpêwimikot" class="vta" gcat="3o3sTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="shame_by_speech" stem="nêpêwim" suffix="-ikot">êh-nêpêwimikot</w>
<w canon="oskinîkiskwêwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="young_woman" stem="oskinîkiskwêw" suffix="-a">oskinîkiskwêwah</w>
,
<w canon="ê-wî-kakwê-isîhkawât" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj wî|will kakwê|try_to" sgloss="bother_thus" stem="isîhkaw" suffix="-ât">ê-wîh-kakwê-isîhkawât</w>
,
<q>
<w canon="osâm" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="too_much" stem="osâm">osâm</w>
<w canon="tâpwê" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="truly" stem="tâpwê">tâpwê</w>
<w canon="wiya" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="WIYA" stem="wiya">wiyah</w>
<w canon="êkâ" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not_to" stem="êkâ">êkâ</w>
<w canon="êhtakohk" class="vii" gcat="0sIIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="exist" stem="takon" suffix="-k">êhtakohk</w>
<w canon="kâ-ocikihkwêyan" class="vai" gcat="2sAIcnj" preverbs="kâ|cnj" sgloss="have_scarred_face" stem="ocikihkwê" suffix="-yan">k-ôcikihkwêyan</w>
,
<w canon="ka-nôcîhkawin" class="vta" gcat="2s1sTA" preverbs="ka|will" sgloss="woo" stem="nôcîhkaw" suffix="-in">kah-nôcîhkawin</w>
,</q>
<w canon="ê-itikot" class="vta" gcat="3o3sTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="say_to" stem="it" suffix="-ikot">êh-itikot</w>
.
<gloss>Another young man went off alone, because a young woman had taunted him to shame when he paid court to her, saying to him, “Truly, if it were not that you are pock-marked on your face, you might woo me with success.”</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="3">

<seg n="3.1">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="sipwêtatwêmôw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="go_off_weeping" stem="sipwêtatwêmo" suffix="-w">sipwêtatwêmôw</w>
,
<w canon="tahki" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="always" stem="tahki">tahkih</w>
<w canon="nayêstaw" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="only" stem="nayêstaw">nayêstaw</w>
<w canon="ê-mâtot" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="cry" stem="mâto" suffix="-t">êh-mâtot</w>
.
<gloss>At that he went off weeping, and wept off alone all the time.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="3.2">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="kêtahtawê" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="at_times" stem="kêtahtawê">kêtahtawê</w>
<w canon="kâ-miskawât" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTAcnj" preverbs="kâ|cnj" sgloss="find" stem="miskaw" suffix="-ât">kâ-miskawât</w>
<w canon="ayîsiyiniwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="person" stem="ayisiyiniw" suffix="-a">ayîsiyiniwah</w>
.
<gloss>Then presently he found some people.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="4">

<seg n="4.1">
<q>
<w canon="tânêhki" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="why" stem="tânêhki">tânêhk</w>
<w canon="ôma" class="dem" gcat="0sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="ôma">ômah</w>
<w canon="kâ-ôh-mâtoyan" class="vai" gcat="2sAIcnj" preverbs="kâ|cnj ôh|thence" sgloss="cry" stem="mâto" suffix="-yan">k-ôh-mâtôyan</w>
?</q>
<gloss>“Why are you weeping like this?”</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="5">

<seg n="5.1">
<q>
<w canon="ê-nêpêwimit" class="vta" gcat="3s1sTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="shame_by_speech" stem="nêpêwim" suffix="-it">êh-nêpêyimit</w>
<w canon="iskwêw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="woman" stem="iskwêw" suffix="0">iskwêw</w>
,
<q>
<w canon="tâpwê" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="truly" stem="tâpwê">tâpwê</w>
<w canon="wiya" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="WIYA" stem="wiya">wiyah</w>
<w canon="êkâ" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not_to" stem="êkâ">êkâ</w>
<w canon="ihtakohk" class="vai" gcat="xAIcnj" sgloss="exist" stem="ihtako" suffix="-hk">ihtakohk</w>
<w canon="kâ-ocikihkwêyin" class="vai" gcat="2sAIcnj" preverbs="kâ|cnj" sgloss="have_scarred_face" stem="ocikihkwê" suffix="-yan">k-ôcikihkwêyin</w>
,
<w canon="ka-isîhkawin" class="vta" gcat="2s1sTA" preverbs="ka|will" sgloss="bother_thus" stem="isîhkaw" suffix="-in">kah-isîhkawin</w>
,</q>
<w canon="ê-isit" class="vta" gcat="3s1sTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="say_to" stem="it" suffix="-it">êh-isit</w>
.</q>
<gloss>“Because a woman has taunted me to shame, saying to me, 'Truly, if it were not that you are pock-marked in your face, you might woo me.'”</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="6">

<seg n="6.1">
<q>
<w canon="hâw" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="now" stem="hâw">hâw</w>
,
<w canon="nôsisê" class="nda" extra="voc" gcat="3sNDAof1svoc" prefix="1" sgloss="grandchild" stem="ôsisim">nôsisê</w>
,
<w canon="mahti" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="let's_see" stem="mahti">maht</w>
<w canon="êyiwêhk" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="just_in_case" stem="kêyiwêhk">êyiwêhk</w>
<w canon="nika-kotêyihtên" class="vti" gcat="1sTI" prefix="1" preverbs="ka|will" sgloss="try_in_mind" stem="kotêyiht" suffix="-ên">nika-kotêyihtên</w>
.</q>
<gloss>“Why, grandchild, let me at any rate see what I can do for this.”</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="7">

<seg n="7.1">
<w canon="matotisânihkêw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="make_sweat_lodge" stem="matotisânihkê" suffix="-w">matotisânihkêw</w>
.
<gloss>He built a sweat-lodge.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="7.2">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="tihkisam" class="vti" gcat="3sTI" sgloss="melt_down" stem="tihkis" suffix="-am">tihkisam</w>
<w canon="pimiy" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="fat" stem="pimiy" suffix="0">pimiy</w>
,
<w canon="wâkayôsi-pimiy" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" prenouns="wâkayôsi|bear" sgloss="fat" stem="pimiy" suffix="0">wâkayôsi-pimiy</w>
;
<w canon="wiyâkanihk" class="ni" gcat="0locNI" sgloss="dish" stem="wiyâkan" suffix="-ihk">wiyâkanihk</w>
<w canon="astâw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="place_there" stem="astâ" suffix="-w">astâw</w>
.
<gloss>Then he melted some fat, bear's-grease; he put it in a bowl.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="7.3">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="tahkopitam" class="vti" gcat="3sTI" sgloss="tie_fast" stem="tahkopit" suffix="-am">tahkopitam</w>
<w canon="maskosiya" class="ni" gcat="0pNI" sgloss="grass" stem="maskosiy" suffix="-a">maskosiyah</w>
.
<gloss>Then he tied up some herbs.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="8">

<seg n="8.1">
<q>
<w canon="hâw" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="now" stem="hâw">hâw</w>
,
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="matotisitân" class="vai" gcat="1iAIimp" sgloss="hold_sweat_lodge" stem="matotisi" suffix="-tân">matotisitân</w>
!</q>
<w canon="itêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="say_to" stem="it" suffix="-êw">itêw</w>
.
<gloss>“Come, now let us take a sweat-bath!” he told him.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="9">

<seg n="9.1">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="kêtayôwinisêw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="take_off_clothes" stem="kêtayowinisê" suffix="-w">kêtayôwinisêw</w>
<w canon="oskinîkiw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="young_man" stem="oskinîkiw" suffix="0">oskinîkiw</w>
.
<gloss>Then the youth took off his clothes.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="9.2">
<w canon="pîhtokêwak" class="vai" gcat="3pAI" sgloss="enter" stem="pîhtikwê" suffix="-wak">pîhtokêwak</w>
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="matotisânihk" class="ni" gcat="0locNI" sgloss="sweat_lodge" stem="matotisân" suffix="-ihk">matotisânihk</w>
,
<w canon="pimiy" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="fat" stem="pimiy" suffix="0">pmiy</w>
<w canon="mîna" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="also" stem="mîna">mina</w>
<w canon="ôma" class="dem" gcat="0sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="ôma">ôma</w>
,
<w canon="masko-pimiy" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="bear_fat" stem="masko-pimiy" suffix="0">masko-pimiy</w>
.
<gloss>Then they entered the sweat-lodge, with that fat, that bear's-grease.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="9.3">
<w canon="akwanahamwân" class="vti" gcat="3sTIrel3o" sgloss="cover" stem="akwanah" suffix="-amwân">akwanahamwân</w>
<w canon="omatotisâniwâw" class="ni" gcat="0sNIof3p" prefix="3" sgloss="sweat_lodge" stem="matotisân" suffix="-iwâw">omatotisâniwâw</w>
.
<gloss>Their companions covered their sweatlodge for them.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="9.4">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="êkosi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="thus" stem="êkosi">êkos</w>
<w canon="ê-sîkahasiniyêt" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="pour_onto_stone" stem="sîkahasiniyê" suffix="-t">ê-sîkahasiniyêt</w>
<w canon="kisêyiniw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="old_man" stem="kisêyiniw" suffix="0">kisêyiniw</w>
,
<w canon="ê-pôh-pôtâtât" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj dupH|H.REDUP" sgloss="blow_at" stem="pôtât" suffix="-ât">êh-pôh-pôtâtât</w>
<w canon="oskinîkiwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="young_man" stem="oskinîkiw" suffix="-a">oskinîkiwah</w>
,
<w canon="piyis" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="finally" stem="piyis">piyis</w>
<w canon="namôya" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="namôya">namoya</w>
<w canon="ta-ihtakoniyiw" class="vii" gcat="0oII" preverbs="ta|FUT" sgloss="exist" stem="ihtakon" suffix="-yiw">t-êhtakoniyiw</w>
<w canon="ôma" class="dem" gcat="0sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="ôma">omah</w>
<w canon="kâ-ocikisiyit" class="vai" gcat="3oAIcnj" preverbs="kâ|cnj" sgloss="be_scarred" stem="ocikisi" suffix="-yit">k-ôcikisiyit</w>
.
<gloss>Thereupon, when the old man poured the fat on the stone, and kept blowing on the youth, at last the pock-marks on his face began to disappear.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="9.5">
<w canon="piyis" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="finally" stem="piyis">piyis</w>
<w canon="ê-mêstinahk" class="vti" gcat="3sTIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="use_up" stem="mêstin" suffix="-ahk">êh-mêstinahk</w>
<w canon="pimiy" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="fat" stem="pimiy" suffix="0">pimiy</w>
<w canon="ôma" class="dem" gcat="0sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="ôma">ômah</w>
,
<w canon="mîna" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="also" stem="mîna">mîna</w>
<w canon="kîhtwâm" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="again" stem="kîhtwâm">kîhtwâm</w>
<w canon="pîhtokatâwân" class="vai" gcat="3sAIrel3" sgloss="take_indoors" stem="pîhtokwatâ" suffix="-wân">pîhtokatâwân</w>
.
<gloss>When he had used up that fat, some more was handed in to them.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="9.6">
<w canon="êyoko" class="pr" gcat="PR" sgloss="that_one" stem="êwako">êyôkw</w>
<w canon="ê-mêstinahk" class="vti" gcat="3sTIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="use_up" stem="mêstin" suffix="-ahk">êh-mâstinahk</w>
,
<w canon="âsay" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="already" stem="âsay">âsay</w>
<w canon="nama" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="nama">nama</w>
<w canon="kêkway" class="pr" gcat="0sPR" sgloss="something" stem="kîkway">kêkway</w>
<w canon="ihtakoniyiw" class="vii" gcat="0oII" sgloss="exist" stem="ihtakon" suffix="-yiw">ihtakoniyiw</w>
<w canon="ocikisiwin" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="scarredness" stem="ocikisiwin" suffix="0">ôcikisiwin</w>
.
<gloss>When he had used this up, his pock-marks were gone.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="9.7">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="ê-pâskît" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="come_from_under" stem="pâskî" suffix="-t">êh-paskît</w>
,
<w canon="namôya" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="namôya">namoya</w>
<w canon="kakêtihk" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="a_few" stem="kakêtihk">kakêtihk</w>
<w canon="ta-kahkâpêwiw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" preverbs="ta|FUT" sgloss="be_of_whole_body" stem="kahkâpêwi" suffix="-w">ta-kahkâpêwiw</w>
<w canon="oskinîkiw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="young_man" stem="oskinîkiw" suffix="0">oskinîkiw</w>
.
<gloss>And when he opened the lodge, whole and without flaw in body was the youth.</gloss>
<note>LB on {kakêtihk}: Unknown word</note>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="10">

<seg n="10.1">
<q>
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="ka-kîwân" class="vai" gcat="2sAI" preverbs="ka|will" sgloss="go_home" stem="kîwê" suffix="-n">ka-kîwân</w>
,
<w canon="nôsisê" class="nda" extra="voc" gcat="3sNDAof1svoc" prefix="1" sgloss="grandchild" stem="ôsisim">nôsisê</w>
,</q>
<w canon="itik" class="vta" gcat="3o3sTA" sgloss="say_to" stem="it" suffix="-ik">itik</w>
<w canon="ôhi" class="dem" gcat="3oDEM" sgloss="this" stem="awa" suffix="-3o">ôhi</w>
<w canon="kâ-kî-nitawihikot" class="vta" gcat="3o3sTAcnj" preverbs="kâ|cnj kî|PAST" sgloss="doctor" stem="nitawih" suffix="-ikot">kâ-kîh-natawihikot</w>
;
<gloss>“Now you will go home, my grandchild,” he was told by him who had doctored him;</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="10.2">
<q>
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="sipwêhtê" class="vai" gcat="2sAIimp" sgloss="leave" stem="sipwêhtê" suffix="0">sipwêhtêh</w>
;
<w canon="iskwêw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="woman" stem="iskwêw" suffix="0">iskwêw</w>
<w canon="ana" class="dem" gcat="3sDEM" sgloss="that" stem="ana">anah</w>
<w canon="kâ-kî-kîhkâmisk" class="vta" gcat="3s2sTAcnj" preverbs="kâ|cnj kî|PAST" sgloss="scold" stem="kîhkâm" suffix="-isk">kâ-kîh-kîhkâmisk</w>
<w canon="ka-nahâpason" class="vai" gcat="2sAI" preverbs="ka|will" sgloss="smell_right" stem="nahâpaso" suffix="-n">ka-nahâpason</w>
,
<w canon="wî-pê-itohtêci" class="vai" gcat="3sAIsubjunc" preverbs="wî|will pê|thence" sgloss="go" stem="itohtê" suffix="-ci">wîh-pêy-itohtêci</w>
<w canon="kisiwâk" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="nearby" stem="kisiwâk">kisiwâk</w>
,</q>
<w canon="itik" class="vta" gcat="3o3sTA" sgloss="say_to" stem="it" suffix="-ik">itik</w>
<w canon="omosôma" class="nda" gcat="3oNDAof3s" prefix="3" sgloss="grandfather" stem="mosôm" suffix="-a">omosôma</w>
.
<gloss>“Now depart; your sense of smell will tell you when that woman who insulted you is coming near,” his grandfather told him.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="10.3">
<w canon="kiskinôhamâk" class="vta" gcat="3o3sTA" sgloss="teach" stem="kiskinahamaw" suffix="-ik">kiskinôhamâk</w>
<w canon="ta-ispinêmât" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTAcnj" preverbs="ta|FUT" sgloss="berate" stem="ispinêm" suffix="-ât">t-êspinêmât</w>
.
<gloss>He taught him how to scold her.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="11">

<seg n="11.1">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="kâ-kîwêt" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="kâ|cnj" sgloss="go_home" stem="kîwê" suffix="-t">kâ-kîwêt</w>
.
<gloss>Then he went home.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="11.2">
<w canon="takohtêw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="arrive" stem="takohtê" suffix="-w">takohtêw</w>
<w canon="wîkiwâhk" class="ndi" gcat="0locNDIof3p" prefix="3" sgloss="house" stem="îk" suffix="-iwâhk">wîkiwâhk</w>
.
<gloss>He came to their camp.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="12">

<seg n="12.1">
<q>
<w canon="wahwâ" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="oh_my" stem="wahwâ">wahwâ</w>
!</q>
<w canon="itwêwak" class="vai" gcat="3pAI" sgloss="say" stem="itwê" suffix="-wak">itwêwak</w>
<w canon="ayîsiyiniwak" class="na" gcat="3pNA" sgloss="person" stem="ayisiyiniw" suffix="-ak">ayîsiyiniwak</w>
;
<q>
<w canon="mistahi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="greatly" stem="mistahi">mistahi</w>
<w canon="miyosiw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="be_good" stem="miyosi" suffix="-w">miyosiw</w>
<w canon="oskinîkiw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="young_man" stem="oskinîkiw" suffix="0">oskinîkiw</w>
<w canon="kâ-kî-sipwêhtêt" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="kâ|cnj kî|PAST" sgloss="leave" stem="sipwêhtê" suffix="-t">kâ-kîh-sipwêhtêt</w>
.</q>
<gloss>“Dear me!” said the people; “Very handsome is the young man who went away.”</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="13">

<seg n="13.1">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="awa" class="dem" gcat="3sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="awa">aw</w>
<w canon="iskwêw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="woman" stem="iskwêw" suffix="0">îskwêw</w>
<w canon="kâ-kî-pakwâtât" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTAcnj" preverbs="kâ|cnj kî|PAST" sgloss="hate" stem="pakwât" suffix="-ât">kâ-kîh-pakwâtât</w>
<w canon="maskisinihkêsiw" class="vai" gcat="3sAIdim" sgloss="make_moccasins" stem="maskisinihkê" suffix="-siw">maskisinihkêsiw</w>
,
<w canon="ê-wî-nitawi-miyât" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj wî|will nitawi|go_to" sgloss="give_to" stem="miy" suffix="-ât">ê-wîh-ntawi-miyât</w>
.
<gloss>Then the woman who had scorned him made some moccasins to give him.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="13.2">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="ê-kîsihtât" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="finish" stem="kîsîhtâ" suffix="-t">êh-kîsihtât</w>
,
<w canon="itohtêw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="go" stem="itohtê" suffix="-w">itohtêw</w>
.
<gloss>When she had finished them, she went there.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="13.3">
<w canon="kêswân" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="by_coincidence" stem="kêswân">kêswân</w>
<w canon="oskinîkiw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="young_man" stem="oskinîkiw" suffix="0">oskinîkiw</w>
<w canon="wayawîw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="go_outside" stem="wayawî" suffix="-w">wayawîw</w>
;
<w canon="wâpamêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="see" stem="wâpam" suffix="-êw">wâpamêw</w>
.
<gloss>Just then the youth was going out of his tent; he saw her.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="13.4">
<w canon="pê-âkwâskâk" class="vta" gcat="3o3sTA" preverbs="pê|thence" sgloss="head_off" stem="âkwâskaw" suffix="-ik">pêy-âkwâskâk</w>
<w canon="iskwêwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="woman" stem="iskwêw" suffix="-a">iskwêwah</w>
.
<gloss>The woman came to head him off.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="14">

<seg n="14.1">
<q>
<w canon="nah" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="take" stem="nah">nah</w>
<w canon="ôhi" class="dem" gcat="3oDEM" sgloss="this" stem="awa" suffix="-3o">ôh</w>
<w canon="êyiwêhk" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="just_in_case" stem="kêyiwêhk">êyiwêhk</w>
,</q>
<w canon="itik" class="vta" gcat="3o3sTA" sgloss="say_to" stem="it" suffix="-ik">itik</w>
.
<gloss>“Here is a little present for you,” she said to him.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="15">

<seg n="15.1">
<w canon="otinam" class="vti" gcat="3sTI" sgloss="take" stem="otin" suffix="-am">otinam</w>
;
<w canon="kwâhciwêpinam" class="vti" gcat="3sTI" sgloss="fling_aside" stem="kwâhciwêpin" suffix="-am">kwâhciwêpinam</w>
.
<gloss>He took them and flung them aside.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="16">

<seg n="16.1">
<q>
<w canon="hêy" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="hey" stem="hêy">hêy</w>
,
<w canon="nika-wî-nipin" class="vai" gcat="1sAI" prefix="1" preverbs="ka|will wî|will" sgloss="die" stem="nipi" suffix="-n">nika-wîh-nipin</w>
,</q>
<w canon="itwêw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="say" stem="itwê" suffix="-w">itwêw</w>
<w canon="iskwêw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="woman" stem="iskwêw" suffix="0">iskwêw</w>
<w canon="awa" class="dem" gcat="3sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="awa">awa</w>
.
<gloss>“Oh dear, I wish I were dead,” said the woman.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="17">

<seg n="17.1">
<q>
<w canon="namôya" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="namôya">namoya</w>
<w canon="niya" class="pr" gcat="1sPR" sgloss="I" stem="niya">niya</w>
<w canon="êkosi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="thus" stem="êkosi">êkosi</w>
<w canon="nôh-itwân" class="vai" gcat="1sAI" prefix="1" preverbs="ôh|thence" sgloss="say" stem="itwê" suffix="-n">nôh-itwân</w>
,
<w canon="ê-kîhkâmiyan" class="vta" gcat="2s1sTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="scold" stem="kîhkâm" suffix="-iyan">êh-kîhkâmiyan</w>
,</q>
<w canon="itêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="say_to" stem="it" suffix="-êw">itêw</w>
<w canon="oskinîkiw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="young_man" stem="oskinîkiw" suffix="0">oskinîkiw</w>
.
<gloss>“I did not say anything like that when you insulted me,” the youth told her.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="18">

<seg n="18.1">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="kîwêw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="go_home" stem="kîwê" suffix="-w">kîwêw</w>
<w canon="awa" class="dem" gcat="3sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="awa">ôw</w>
<w canon="oskinîkiskwêw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="young_woman" stem="oskinîkiskwêw" suffix="0">oskinîkiskwêw</w>
;
<w canon="nêpêwisiw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="be_ashamed" stem="nêpêwisi" suffix="-w">nêpêwisiw</w>
.
<gloss>Then the young woman went home; she was ashamed.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="18.2">
<w canon="têpiskâyiki" class="vii" gcat="0oIIsubjunc" prefix="IC" sgloss="be_night" stem="tipiskâ" suffix="-yiki">têpiskâyikih</w>
<w canon="nitawâpamêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="go_to_see" stem="nitawâpam" suffix="-êw">ntawâpamêw</w>
.
<gloss>Of a night she would go to see him.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="19">

<seg n="19.1">
<q>
<w canon="pê-wîhcêkan" class="vii" gcat="0sII" preverbs="pê|thence" sgloss="smell_bad" stem="wîhcêkan" suffix="0">pê-wîhcêkan</w>
,</q>
<w canon="itwêyiwa" class="vai" gcat="3oAI" sgloss="say" stem="itwê" suffix="-yiwa">itwêyiwah</w>
,
<w canon="kisiwâk" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="nearby" stem="kisiwâk">kisiwâk</w>
<w canon="êtohtêci" class="vai" gcat="3sAIsubjunc" prefix="IC" sgloss="go" stem="itohtê" suffix="-ci">êtohtêcih</w>
.
<gloss>“A nasty smell is coming this way,” he would say whenever she came near.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="19.2">
<w canon="nama" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="nama">nama</w>
<w canon="nânitaw" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="simply" stem="nânitaw">nânitaw</w>
<w canon="isi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="thus" stem="isi">isih</w>
<w canon="kî-wâpamêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" preverbs="kî|PAST" sgloss="see" stem="wâpam" suffix="-êw">kîh-wâpamêw</w>
<w canon="oskinîkiwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="young_man" stem="oskinîkiw" suffix="-a">oskinîkiwah</w>
.
<gloss>She was not able to have any converse with the youth.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="20">

<seg n="20.1">
<w canon="mîna" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="also" stem="mîna">min</w>
<w canon="êwako" class="pr" gcat="PR" sgloss="that_one" stem="êwako">êwakô</w>
<w canon="otâcimôwiniwâw" class="ni" gcat="0sNIof3p" prefix="3" sgloss="story" stem="âcimowin" suffix="-iwâw">otâcimôwiniwâw</w>
<w canon="ayahciyiniwak" class="na" gcat="3pNA" sgloss="Blackfoot" stem="ayahciyiniw" suffix="-ak">iyahciyiniwak</w>
,
<w canon="ê-kî-mamâhtâwisicik" class="vai" gcat="3pAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj kî|PAST" sgloss="have_supernatural_power" stem="mamâhtâwisi" suffix="-cik">ê-kîh-mamâhtâwisicik</w>
<w canon="kayâs" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="long_ago" stem="kayâs">kayâs</w>
<w canon="ayahciyiniwak" class="na" gcat="3pNA" sgloss="Blackfoot" stem="ayahciyiniw" suffix="-ak">ayahciyiniwak</w>
,
<w canon="mêkwâc" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="while" stem="mêkwâc">mêkwâc</w>
<w canon="paskwâwi-mostoso-wiyâs" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" prenouns="paskwâwi-mostoso|bison" sgloss="meat" stem="wiyâs" suffix="0">paskwâwi-mostoso-wiyâs</w>
<w canon="ê-mîcicik" class="vai" gcat="3pAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="eat" stem="mîci" suffix="-cik">êh-mîcicik</w>
.
<gloss>This too is a Blackfoot story, of how the Blackfoot of old had mystic power, when they used to eat buffalo-meat.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="20.2">
<w canon="êyakonik" class="pr" gcat="3pPR" sgloss="that_one" stem="êwako" suffix="-3p">êyakonik</w>
<w canon="otôtamôwiniwâw" class="ni" gcat="0sNIof3p" prefix="3" sgloss="way_of_doing" stem="tôtamôwin" suffix="-iwâw">otôtamôwiniwâw</w>
<w canon="mîna" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="also" stem="mîna">mînah</w>
<w canon="ayahciyiniwak" class="na" gcat="3pNA" sgloss="Blackfoot" stem="ayahciyiniw" suffix="-ak">iyahciyiniwak</w>
<w canon="kâ-kîsihtâyân" class="vai" gcat="1sAIcnj" preverbs="kâ|cnj" sgloss="finish" stem="kîsîhtâ" suffix="-yân">kâ-kîsihtâyân</w>
.
<gloss>That of which I have just finished telling is another custom of the Blackfoot.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="20.3">
<w canon="mâmaskâc" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="strangely" stem="mâmaskâc">mâmaskâc</w>
<w canon="kîpa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="early" stem="kîpa">kîpah</w>
<w canon="êkâ" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not_to" stem="êkâ">êk</w>
<w canon="ê-ihtakoniyik" class="vii" gcat="0oIIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="exist" stem="ihtakon" suffix="-yik">êh-ihtakwaniyik</w>
<w canon="ocikihkwêwin" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="face_scars" stem="ocikihkwêwin" suffix="0">ôcikihkwêwin</w>
.
<gloss>It is wonderful that in a short time the pock-marks disappeared from his face.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="20.4">
<w canon="wiya" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="WIYA" stem="wiya">wiy</w>
<w canon="êwako" class="pr" gcat="PR" sgloss="that_one" stem="êwako">êwakô</w>
<w canon="nikîsihtân" class="vai" gcat="1sAI" prefix="1" sgloss="finish" stem="kîsîhtâ" suffix="-n">nikîsihtân</w>
<w canon="âcimôwin" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="story" stem="âcimowin" suffix="0">âcimôwin</w>
.
<gloss>So now I have finished this story.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>
</body>
</text>
